World "GroupBasicsPset"
Title "Group Basics Problem Set"

Introduction
"
Welcome to the **Group Basics Problem Set** — your first practice world.

No new theorems or tactics to learn here, just fresh problems using
the tools you've already built. The goal is fluency: recognizing which
tool to reach for when a problem looks different from anything you've
practiced before.

Your full toolkit is available — including the `group` tactic, which
is back after its absence in Group Basics. Level 1 demonstrates its
power. For the remaining levels, `group` is disabled to keep you sharp
on manual techniques.

The boss: extend the shoes-and-socks lemma from two factors to three.
"
